Look up the ARM CPU name via /sys/bus/event_source/devices first.

Upstream get_cpuName() scans /sys/devices/ one directory deep looking
for an "arm*" entry. That worked on pre-6.x kernels that exposed the
PMU at /sys/devices/armv8_cortex_aNN, but 6.x moved the node under
/sys/devices/platform/arm-pmu/armv8_cortex_aNN, so the shallow scan
returns nothing on modern aarch64 hosts. Result on jonerix Pi 5
(kernel 6.18.22-v8-16k+): btop shows no CPU name, while the same
binary on a Pi 4 / 6.1 kernel correctly shows "Cortex A72".

The kernel still registers the PMU under /sys/bus/event_source/devices/
with the same "armv8_cortex_a76" name on every kernel version we
care about (that path is a symlink into the moved location on 6.x),
so prefer it and keep the /sys/devices/ scan as a legacy fallback.

Tested on:
  * arfur (Pi 4, Debian, kernel 6.1.38-v8+):           "Cortex A72"
  * jonerix-tormenta (Pi 5, jonerix, 6.18.22-v8-16k+): "Cortex A76"

--- a/src/linux/btop_collect.cpp
+++ b/src/linux/btop_collect.cpp
@@ -374,19 +374,31 @@ namespace Cpu {
 				cpuinfo.ignore(1);
 				getline(cpuinfo, name);
 			}
-			else if (fs::exists("/sys/devices")) {
-				for (const auto& d : fs::directory_iterator("/sys/devices")) {
-					if (string(d.path().filename()).starts_with("arm")) {
-						name = d.path().filename();
-						break;
-					}
-				}
-				if (not name.empty()) {
-					auto name_vec = ssplit(name, '_');
-					if (name_vec.size() < 2) return capitalize(name);
-					else return capitalize(name_vec.at(1)) + (name_vec.size() > 2 ? ' ' + capitalize(name_vec.at(2)) : "");
-				}
-
-			}
+			else {
+				// Prefer /sys/bus/event_source/devices/ — stable across kernel
+				// versions. 6.x moved the PMU node from /sys/devices/armv8_cortex_aNN
+				// to /sys/devices/platform/arm-pmu/armv8_cortex_aNN, which the old
+				// shallow scan missed on modern aarch64. The event-source bus still
+				// carries the same "armv8_cortex_aNN" name on both layouts.
+				const char *pmu_dirs[] = {
+					"/sys/bus/event_source/devices",
+					"/sys/devices",
+				};
+				for (const char *dir : pmu_dirs) {
+					if (not fs::exists(dir)) continue;
+					for (const auto& d : fs::directory_iterator(dir)) {
+						if (string(d.path().filename()).starts_with("arm")) {
+							name = d.path().filename();
+							break;
+						}
+					}
+					if (not name.empty()) break;
+				}
+				if (not name.empty()) {
+					auto name_vec = ssplit(name, '_');
+					if (name_vec.size() < 2) return capitalize(name);
+					else return capitalize(name_vec.at(1)) + (name_vec.size() > 2 ? ' ' + capitalize(name_vec.at(2)) : "");
+				}
+			}

 			name = trim_name(name);
